- "completed their journey to air" refers to episodes that have the status 'aired';
- "maintaining legal compliance" refers to episodes with the legal status 'compliant';
- "diverse ensemble" refers to shows that have more than one distinct host.

- 'Captured the hearts of its audience the most' refers to the episode with the highest number of non-anonymous ratings;
- 'Chorus of non-anonymous ratings' indicates the count of ratings where the user's identity is known;
- 'Key details' include the episode title, show name, type of show, host name, average rating, and the count of non-anonymous ratings.

- "shining stars" refers to the primary hosts;
- "celebrated episodes" refers to the episodes with the highest ratings;
- "each show" refers to the unique shows identified by the show ID.

- "crowning jewels" refers to the episodes with the highest average ratings;
- "stand tall" means being the best or most highly rated;
- "among all episodes of their respective shows" indicates that the ranking is done within each show.
